steps.instruction:
### Making The Dough
- Put 2 cups of flour, 3/4 teaspoons of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of any kind of yeast, and 1 tablespoon of olive oil into a bowl
- Mix well, till a shaggy dough forms with no dry spots (about 30 to 45 seconds in a mixer, about 1 minute by hand)
- Scrape the sides of the bowl
- Form the dough into a ball and cover the bowl
- Let sit for 5 minutes

### Folding
- uncover the dough
- Put your *wet* hand between the bowl and the dough
- Pull the dough as if you were going to pull it our of the bowl, but your going to pull it and stretch the bottom of the dough over the top
- Turn the bowl 90 degrees
- Repeat the fold and turn 3 more times
- Cover the Bowl and let sit for 5 minutes
- Fold and turn 4 more times
- Cover and wait 5 minutes
- Fold and turn 4 more times
- Cover the dough and let rest for 40 minutes
- Put in the fridge for a minimum of 12 hours and a max of 72 hours

### Baking
- About 3 Hours before you want to serve your pizza, prepare your pan
- Pour 1.5 tablespoons of olive oil onto a well-seasoned cast iron skillet that is 10 to 11 inches in diameter across the top
    - If you don't have a cast iron skillet a similar size cake pan will do
- Use finger and/or a paper towel to move the oil evenly across the pan, including the edges
- Transfer the dough to the pan and flip the dough once to coast both sides of the dough with oil
- Press the dough to the edges of the pan
    - If the dough resists and springs back, just let it sit for about 15 minutes and try again
- Cover the crust and let it rise for 2 hours at room temperature
- About 30 minutes before baking place one rack at the bottom of the oven and on toward the top (about 4 to 5 inches from the heating element)
- Preheat to 450F
- When you're reading to make your pizza, sprinkle about 3/4 of the mozzarella onto the crust, dollop spoonfuls of sauce over the cheese, then sprinkle the remaining mozzarella
- Bake for 18 to 20 minutes on the bottom rack or until the cheese is bubbling and the bottom edges of the crust are a rich golden brown
    - If the bottom is brown but the top seems pale, put the pizza on the top rack for 2 to 4 minutes
    - If the top seems fine but the bottom isn't brown, leave on the bottom rack for 2 to 4 minutes
- Take the pizza out, and let cool before serving
